ir setup in Gradle.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra dependency or Docker service is needed for meaningful Vert.x Web Client coverage; loopback HTTP tests are enough. However, the resolved 5.0.1 runtime still pulls Netty 4.2.x, so native-image runs on JDK 25 need the same Netty unsafe-access system properties already used for 5.0.0.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Use local Vert.x HttpServer/WebClient tests for coverage; do not require external network services. Ensure nativeTest/runtime execution for io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 sets -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true, e.g. extend the existing 5.0.0 nativeTest runtimeArgs guard to include 5.0.1.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 resolves io.netty 4.2.2.Final through vertx-core; omitting the JDK 25 unsafe-access properties may keep native-image runtime tests failing despite valid metadata.\",\n    \"OAuth2WebClient coverage would require the optional io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2 dependency, but core meaningful WebClient coverage does not require it.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a40e438ad0f95f6016a415e16d8708194a627401d1742565a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1274, "output": 1190, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24992, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782668805370, "responseId": "resp_0a40e438ad0f95f6016a415e05dfe481949632d19aaf8a8c51"}}
